I finally typed those magic words today! ❤️

And now I will brush my hair for the first time in 3 days. There is a big glass of wine in my very near future. 🥂

Title to come, cover to come, I can tell you literally nothing. 😆 Or maybe I can… it’s romantic, and there’s snow, and there’s this guy who… nope, that’s all. 🤐❄️❤️
More as soon as I’m allowed! x

#amnotwritingtomorrow #newbooknews #romance #lovestory #wheresthewine

Happy 2023! 🥂 Wishing you all health, peace and happiness. 

New year, gorgeous new clip to hold my edit notes together as I dive back into work on the next book! 

I secretly love the editing process, I always think of it as a magic wand highlighting things I cannot see because I’m too close to the story. 🪄
Isn’t the clip fabulous? A Christmas gift from my lovely sis, who is writing her first novel this year! I foresee daily morning FaceTime calls to fire each other up. 🔥💻 

No resolutions from me, just to work hard and appreciate how lucky I am to do a job I love so much it doesn’t feel like work. 
#happynewyear #amediting

Goodbye again, my pretties! 

We always eek out Christmas cheer until the very last minute in our house, but it’s 12th night so they’ve gone away for another year now. The house looks so bare, it’s going to take a lot of candles to bring the glow tonight. ❤️

No one could call us minimalist when it comes to baubles, eh? 😆
Christmas books! Adding to my @susiedent shelf ❤️#languagenerd

My writing life today! 

Is it a sign of age that leopard-lined crocs and a heated blanket are sparking joy for me as I work today? It’s snowing out there but I am toasty as a slice of toast.

Hope your Wednesday is going well - stay warm, or cool if you’re lucky enough to be somewhere with blue skies and sunshine today! ❄️☀️❄️

#amediting #crocs #staywarmmittens

Author of ‘One Day in December’ @josiesilverauthor’s new book ‘A Winter in New York’ hits U.S. shelves this October from @randomhouse! To celebrate, we’re excited to reveal the cover, illustrated by @moniqueaimee with art direction from @casacassie and @elenagiavaldicovers. This romance follows a young chef who stumbles on a secret family recipe that might lead her to love. Make sure to add it to your WTR shelf when you follow the link in our bio!

Posted @withregram • @jfkillsdarlings GIVEAWAY ALERT! Book and matching dress! 
.
In One Day in December by @josiesilverauthor, two people circle each other for a decade of missed opportunities while they weigh their what-ifs, work through relationships and job transitions. I really enjoy Silver’s writing, the ways little details like the placement of a painting or a hasty flower selection have weight without feeling heavy-handed in their symbolism. The prose is swift and wryly funny, and Silver isn’t afraid to make her characters imperfect, adding layers of realism to a story with a big romantic heart. I particularly enjoyed the nuances in the central friendship and the heroine’s secondary romance, such that they didn’t feel solely like scaffolding for the central love story. I also enjoyed the heroine’s evolving New Year’s resolutions, depicting a girl emerging from the levity of youth into a woman on the other side of both gains and losses, weighing how to shape her life in meaningful ways. Can't wait to see how this translates to the screen!
.
For the design, I used a trench coat shape to mirror the illustration, with bows for the title, pearl beads for the snow, and ribbon details to suggest the bus and couple. Although I attempted a battery-powered light for the streetlamp, metallic organza captured the romantic feel better, set against a black velvet lamppost.
.

So, what can I tell you about this story? 
Well, it's wintery and it's set in New York. 🙃

It's Iris's story, and it begins when she flees to New York and stumbles across an oddly familiar painted glass door... 

A litle bit festive and a lot romantic, it's a story to curl up with when the nights draw in. I really hope you're going to love it.

Meet Josie Silver: the beloved New York Times Bestselling author of @reesesbookclub selection ONE DAY IN DECEMBER. 🌨️❤️

Two novels and five years later, she’s back with another winter romance, A WINTER IN NEW YORK! Though she’s never visited New York, Silver steeped this story in New York culture, transporting readers to the Lower East Side.

Head to zibbymag.com to learn more about @josiesilverauthor writing process, her favorite romance tropes, and the experience of adapting ONE DAY IN DECEMBER to film!

❤️📚❤️ IT’S US PUBLICATION DAY!

A Winter in New York is released in the USA today, so here I am with it in my unseasonably sunny garden to celebrate! 

It’s amazing to imagine it being shelved in NY bookstores this morning, and appearing like magic in stores from coast to coast. 

It’s always nerve-wracking when the story goes from my head to yours, it becomes something new and different. I hope you love meeting Iris, Gio and the whole Belotti clan! They were a joy to write, my heart goes out there with them today. ❤️

#awinterinnewyork #publicationday #josiesilver

Episode 44: Happy to Meet Josie Silver!

We were so thrilled to chat with the incomparable Josie Silver! We talk all about her new book A Winter in New York, her writing process, how to work writing in around family time, and all of our favorite feel good movies and TV shows. Josie is an absolute delight and we hope you love this episode as much as we love her!
